# Working conventions for this workspace — {DOMAIN} OS

You operate the {DOMAIN} operating system. Your job is not just to file things — it is to keep the
system **current and compounding**, and to decide "done" and "consistent" by evidence (a
`{DOMAIN}-doctor` run), not by feeling. Act autonomously on the rules below. (AGENTS.md is a symlink
to this file.)

## Auto-manage loop (run on new input, without being asked)
1. Place the raw file in its correct home, dated YYYY-MM-DD.
2. Read it.
3. Extract reusable value into `knowledge/` (insights / faqs / decisions).
4. Scan the related {ENTITY}/{PIPELINE} folder; read its README; reconcile.
5. Update everything affected in the SAME turn: entity README dashboards, `{PIPELINE}/_board.md`,
   `artifacts/dashboard.html`, metrics. (never-stale rule)
6. Move folders to match reality (stage changes); update the external system of record if any.
7. Mine for compounding assets (templates, proof, FAQs).
8. Report what changed.

Confirm before inventing {DOMAIN} facts; otherwise just do the routine filing and summarize.

## Never stale (checked, not felt)
If you touched the project, leave it consistent — and "consistent" is what `{DOMAIN}-doctor` reports,
not a feeling. After any change, ask which other files now disagree with reality and update them all.
Run `{DOMAIN}-doctor` to verify; the `{DOMAIN}-janitor` skill runs it + fixes drift on a schedule.
When you touch anything carrying a "draft — confirm" marker, confirm or correct it in the same turn —
burn that debt down instead of letting predictions accrue.

## Compound learning + self-improvement (get smarter every session)
Every session deposits at least one durable learning (a decision, a canonical answer, an insight, or
an improved template/skill). Search `knowledge/` before solving anything — never twice. And improve the
**system**, not just its contents: when the same friction recurs, run `{DOMAIN}-reflect` to turn it
into a new skill, routing row, doctor check, or rule, logged to `operations/improvements.md` (~half
your effort on the system that does the work).

## After work, ask: "skillify this?"
When you finish a task, ask whether it will be done again, need maintaining, or prevent a failure from
recurring. If yes, run the `{DOMAIN}-skillify` skill. It stages a draft in `work/`, extracts the
repeatable process, verifies it, asks for approval, then moves it to `plugin/skills/{name}/SKILL.md`
and repackages. If it's a one-off, the output goes in `work/{project}/YYYY-MM-DD-…/`, never a new
top-level folder.

## Agent compatibility
`plugin/skills/` is the source of truth. `.agents/skills` points there so Cursor and Codex can discover
the same project skills. Do not edit `.agents/skills` directly, and do not create `.cursor/skills`
unless the user explicitly wants a Cursor-only mirror.

## Filing decision tree
1. Reusable instrument (template/script/checklist)? -> `library/`
2. A task that will repeat or need upkeep? -> run `{DOMAIN}-skillify`
3. A finalized output you regenerate (dashboard, recurring report)? -> `artifacts/`
4. A one-off / ad-hoc build (won't repeat)? -> `work/{project}/YYYY-MM-DD-…/`
5. Reusable answer/insight/decision/SOP? -> `knowledge/`
6. Flowing item not yet done? -> `{PIPELINE}/`
7. Tied to a core entity? -> `{ENTITY}/`
8. Outcome/proof? -> `proof/`
9. Raw/idea/draft/published? -> `content/`
10. Canon/source/spec? -> `reference/`
11. Legal/finance/metrics? -> `business/`

## Don't
- Don't duplicate canon; reference `reference/`.
- Don't invent facts the user must own — mark inferred items "draft — confirm".
- Don't leave the system stale after input — run the loop.
